      <p class="faq-question" data-num="1">Is there a player limit for clinics?</p>
      <p class="answer" id="answer-1">Yes, camps are intentionally kept in smaller groups to maximize instruction. Size of clinics will vary.</p>

      <p class="faq-question" data-num="2">What should I bring?</p>
      <p class="answer" id="answer-2">Players should bring full pads, but 90% will be helmet and gloves. These clinics are extremely position focused and concentrates on skills rather than contact.</p>

      <p class="faq-question" data-num="3">Why should I choose Wolf Lacroose Clinics?</p>
      <p class="answer" id="answer-3">Wolf Lacrosse provides campers a unique camp experience. These clinics are extremely structured and endorse a specialized position based curriculum being taught by some of the best players in todayâ€™s game. Improvement and development are the only goal.</p>

      <p class="faq-question" data-num="4">What are the age requirements?</p>
      <p class="answer" id="answer-4">Typically these camps include ages ranging from 6th-11th grade. All campers interested in improving their craft are highly encouraged to attend.</p>

      <p class="faq-question" data-num="5">Who can I contact if my questions isn't in the FAQ?</p>
      <p class="answer" id="answer-5">If we didn't answer your question in the FAQ, feel free to <a href="mailto:jordan.wolf@duke.edu">email us</a> and we'll be happy to get back to you as soon as possible.</p>
